Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips. Drain the @Sweetcorn{75%g} in a #sieve{}. Peel
and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @Mature
Cheddar Cheese{30%g} and @Monterey Jack Cheese{30%g}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the
oil is hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{60%g} and pepper slices. Fry until the
chorizo starts to brown on the outside and the pepper is just soft,
~{3-4%minutes}. Continue to stir while they cook. Once ready, remove to a
#plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Pop the @Tomato Puree{2%tbsp} into a small #bowl{}. Add the garlic and the
@Water{2%tbsp} (see ingredients for amount). Season with a little @salt and
@ground black pepper and mix well to combine. This is your naanizza base sauce.

Divide the sauce between the @Plain Naans{2}. Use a #spoon{} to spread the
sauce all over the naan, leaving a 1cm border around the edge (as the crust).
Top with the chorizo, pepper slices and sweetcorn (see ingredients for amount),
spreading it all out evenly. Then scatter the cheese all over. Pop your
naanizzas onto a #baking tray{} and bake in your oven until the cheese has
melted and is bubbling, ~{6-7%minutes}.

== Balsamic Dressed Rocket ==

While the naanizza bakes, pour the @Balsamic Vinegar{½%tbsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}
for the dressing into a medium bowl (see ingredients for both amounts). Season
with @salt and @ground black pepper and mix well. Just before serving, pop the
@Wild Rocket{40%g} into the bowl with the dressing and toss to coat. Don't do
this too early or the rocket will become soggy.

When ready, remove the naanizzas from the oven. Pop them onto your #plates{} and
serve with the rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!

> This Chorizo, Pepper and Sweetcorn Naanizza is a crowd pleaser and is one to get
> the family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily
> customised to suit the kids too.